I greatly enjoy Checkers. I never been to Rally's, but I assume it's pretty similar in style and many though.  For me, Checkers sells the basic American fast food fare. But, they make their own twist with seasoned French fries and powered funnels cakes (my fav).  They occupy a tiny footprint on a busy street. But, that adds to the ease in which they can fit into diverse urban areas.  Technically they have a dining in area but it was hardly ever used even before COVID19. Now, forget it. Drive through only.  This franchise is kinda ghetto yummy food. I mean that as a compliment.  Don't come here if you are wanting light food options. But, stop by on your "cheat days".
